<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="629" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-17"><hi rend="italic">November 17,
                                    1895</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Jewett telegraphs massacres have begun at Marsovan and Amasia. Poche
                            telegraphs bloody conflict at Aintab. Great fear is entertained at
                            Aleppo. Anxiety of friends of missionaries might be allayed if the
                            Department of State would authorize public statement that I have not
                            needed Department orders to awaken vigilance, as published, but demanded
                            and secured orders, since renewed and executed, to protect Americans
                            everywhere before any massacres began.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>